    <note type="biography">
        <p>Naturalist and gardener. His interest in botany and entomology intensified during an enforced stay in the Cape Colony following a shipwreck. Became gardener to John Milford, Exeter, in 1848. Curator to the Archaeological and Natural History Society of Somerset, 1859–61. Librarian to the Devon and Exeter Institute, 1861–93.</p></note>
